  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the study is:

      to develop a comprehensive biochemical assay for detection of Pompe disease (glycogen storage
      disease type II), to be implemented in the Newborn screening program among the Israeli
      population.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
